KLM says restructuring plan can meet target . KLM Royal Dutch Airlines said on Tuesday its Focus 2000 restructuring programme was on target to increase operating income by 1 . 5 billion guilders over the next three years . " The assessments so far confirm the possibility to structurally improve operating income by 1 . 5 billion guilders over a three - year period , " KLM said . The airline earlier reported third - quarter operating results dwindled to a 19 million guilder loss from a year - earlier 56 million guilder profit , undermined by spiralling fuel costs , a hefty wage bill and increased third party and landing charges . 
